zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533180\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533180\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vuj1665702871233.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vuj1665702871233.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vuj1665702871233.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vuj1665702871233\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n               \n Password Fields\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__password_fields_85450\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">In password fields, the content of the field is not displayed. To define a password field in a Form, set the field syntax to <code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code> (No Display) and use an Edit Box widget for the field.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__p_d25448e1_d25449e1_d25450e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code> is a static property and cannot be changed after the form is displayed. This means that it must be set before the ProcScript <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">edit</span> statement is executed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__p_d25451e1_d25452e1_d25453e1\">You can set the field syntax declaratively in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Syntax</span> field of the field properties, or set it in ProcScript using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldsyntax</span> instruction. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$fieldsyntax(PASSWORD.PERSON.MYMODEL)=\"NDI\"\nedit</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__p_d25454e1_d25455e1_d25456e1\">If you want to prevent the field from being edited, you can also set the field syntax to NED (non-editable) or to NPR (no prompt). Thus, the following combinations all define a password field:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__li_d12617e1_d12618e1_d12619e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__li_d12620e1_d12621e1_d12622e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__li_d12623e1_d12624e1_d12625e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__p_d25457e1_d25458e1_d25459e1\">A password field cannot be created with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">HID</code> (Hide) field syntax, (nor by setting <code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code>). For example, you cannot create a hidden password field and un-hide in later in ProcScript. In this case. it will be a normal field.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__topic_d17412e1_d17413e1_d17414e1_d17415e1_d17416e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d104946e123\">\n                 \n Balloon Tips\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__p_d25463e1_d25464e1_d25465e1\">On some Windows systems, if Caps Lock is on, a tooltip warning may be displayed on an <code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code> field. (It should not be displayed if the field is also set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code>.)</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__fig_d25466e1_d25467e1_d25468e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Caps Lock Balloon Tip</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Caps Lock Balloon Tip on Password Field\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/capslocktooltip.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__p_d25472e1_d25473e1_d25474e1\">This depends on the value of the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">EnableBalloonTips</span> variable in the registry key:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__p_d25475e1_d25476e1_d25477e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Windows/Currentversion/Explorer/Advanced</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vuj1665702871233__p_d25478e1_d25479e1_d25480e1\">If <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">EnableBalloonTips</span> is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>, the tooltip is displayed; if it is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>, the tooltip is not displayed.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jjg1714304600909.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Field Syntax Codes</a><p>Field syntax codes specify the data entry pattern, the allowed characters, and whether fields are mandatory or read-only.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533180\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533180\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Password Fields Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Password Fields In password fields, the content of the field is not displayed. To define a password field in a Form, set the field syntax to NDI (No Display) and use an Edit Box widget for the field. NDI is a static property and cannot be changed after the form is displayed. This means that it must be set before the ProcScript edit statement is executed. You can set the field syntax declaratively in the Syntax field of the field properties, or set it in ProcScript using the $fieldsyntax instruction. For example: $fieldsyntax(PASSWORD.PERSON.MYMODEL)=\"NDI\" edit Copy If you want to prevent the field from being edited, you can also set the field syntax to NED (non-editable) or to NPR (no prompt). Thus, the following combinations all define a password field: NDI NDI , NED NDI , NPR A password field cannot be created with the HID (Hide) field syntax, (nor by setting NDI , NED , and NPR ). For example, you cannot create a hidden password field and un-hide in later in ProcScript. In this case. it will be a normal field. Balloon Tips On some Windows systems, if Caps Lock is on, a tooltip warning may be displayed on an NDI field. (It should not be displayed if the field is also set to NED or NPR .) Figure 1. Caps Lock Balloon Tip This depends on the value of the EnableBalloonTips variable in the registry key: HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Windows/Currentversion/Explorer/Advanced If EnableBalloonTips is set to 1 , the tooltip is displayed; if it is set to 0 , the tooltip is not displayed. Related Links Field Syntax Codes Field syntax codes specify the data entry pattern, the allowed characters, and whether fields are mandatory or read-only. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}